HEADWORD: Kleenex
<hw>Kleenex</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Trademark]</ety> <def>A piece
of soft absorbent tissue paper (usually two or more thin layers) used as
a disposable handkerchief; -- still a current trademark, but often used
generically.</def> <mark>[Trademark]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tissue.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

